public class MultiList
extends java.util.ArrayList<java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Object,java.lang.Object>>

A MultiList works in much the same way as arrays do in PHP. That is, we can have a key of any type with a corresponding value of any type. So we could insert a key-value pair of types , and then later another pair of , and the MultiList will allow this. Furthermore, the MultiList is an array of an array, so we could have the following structure: [0] --> [, ] [, ] [1] --> [, ] [, ] [2] --> [, ] [, ] etc. Where it is structured like so: [array-index] --> [key, value]

Author:
Matthew Kelly (Badgerati).
